Dream, little one, dream

3
00:01:00,476 --> 00:01:06,816
Dream, my little one, dream

4
00:01:07,984 --> 00:01:11,237
Oh, the hunter

5
00:01:11,237 --> 00:01:14,532
In the night

6
00:01:14,490 --> 00:01:19,078
Fills your childish heart

7
00:01:18,995 --> 00:01:22,790
With fright

8
00:01:22,707 --> 00:01:28,546
Fear is only a dream

9
00:01:30,173 --> 00:01:35,178
So dream, little one

10
00:01:35,094 --> 00:01:38,556
Dream

11
00:01:40,057 --> 00:01:43,102
Now, you remember, children,
how I told you last Sunday...

12
00:01:43,060 --> 00:01:46,689
about the good Lord going up into the
mountain and talking to the people...

13
00:01:46,647 --> 00:01:50,776
and how He said, "Blessed are the pure
in heart, for they shall see God"...

14
00:01:50,735 --> 00:01:54,447
and how He said that King Solomon
in all his glory...

15
00:01:54,405 --> 00:01:57,408
was not as beautiful
as the lilies of the field?

16
00:01:57,366 --> 00:02:01,204
And I know you won't forget,
"Judge not lest ye be judged"...

17
00:02:01,162 --> 00:02:03,372
because I explained that to you.

18
00:02:03,372 --> 00:02:07,168
And then the Good Lord
went on to say...

19
00:02:07,126 --> 00:02:10,129
"Beware of false prophets...

20
00:02:10,129 --> 00:02:13,090
which come to you
in sheep's clothing...

21
00:02:13,049 --> 00:02:16,552
but inwardly
they are ravening wolves.

22
00:02:16,469 --> 00:02:19,514
Ye shall know them
by their fruits."

23
00:02:19,472 --> 00:02:21,641
Five, ten, fifteen, twenty,
twenty-five, thirty, thirty-five...

24
00:02:21,641 --> 00:02:24,310
forty, forty-five, fifty, fifty-five,
sixty, sixty-five, seventy...

25
00:02:24,310 --> 00:02:27,730
seventy-five, eighty, eighty-five,
ninety, ninety-five, one hundred!

26
00:02:27,688 --> 00:02:29,982
Here I come, ready or not!

27
00:02:31,442 --> 00:02:33,819
What's wrong?

28
00:02:33,819 --> 00:02:35,988
Hey! Hey!

29
00:02:45,581 --> 00:02:49,335
"A good tree cannot
bring forth evil fruit.

30
00:02:49,335 --> 00:02:53,089
Neither can a corrupt tree
bring forth good fruit.

31
00:02:53,047 --> 00:02:56,801
Wherefore, by their fruits,
ye shall know them."

32
00:02:59,929 --> 00:03:02,515
Well, now, what's it to be, Lord?

33
00:03:02,515 --> 00:03:04,892
Another widow?

34
00:03:04,892 --> 00:03:07,687
How many has it been? Six?

35
00:03:07,687 --> 00:03:11,899
Twelve? I disremember.

36
00:03:15,695 --> 00:03:19,240
You say the word, Lord,
I'm on my way.

37
00:03:26,706 --> 00:03:30,793
You always send me money
to go forth and preach Your Word.

38
00:03:32,211 --> 00:03:36,424
A widow with a little wad of bills
hid away in a sugar bowl.

39
00:03:46,851 --> 00:03:49,770
Lord, I am tired.

40
00:03:49,770 --> 00:03:53,733
Sometimes I wonder
if You really understand, Lord.

41
00:03:55,318 --> 00:03:58,696
Not that you mind the killings.
Your book is full of killings.

42
00:04:00,406 --> 00:04:02,742
But there are things
You do hate, Lord.

43
00:04:02,742 --> 00:04:06,454
Perfume-smelling things,
lacy things...

44
00:04:06,454 --> 00:04:09,123
things with curly hair.

45
00:04:52,750 --> 00:04:57,171
There are too many of them.
You can't kill a world.

46
00:04:58,673 --> 00:05:02,260
You driving a touring car
with a Moundsville license?

47
00:05:02,260 --> 00:05:05,012
Harry Powell, for the theft
of that touring car...

48
00:05:05,012 --> 00:05:08,182
you'll spend 30 days
in the Moundsville Penitentiary.

49
00:05:08,182 --> 00:05:10,893
- Preacher Harry Powell.
- A car thief.

50
00:05:10,852 --> 00:05:15,147
Picked up where you were?
A man of God?

51
00:05:15,064 --> 00:05:16,524
Harry Powell.

52
00:05:38,880 --> 00:05:42,967
- Hold Miss Jenny still.
- Stand still, Miss Jenny.

53
00:05:45,094 --> 00:05:47,263
There. What's so hard about that?

54
00:05:52,143 --> 00:05:53,186
Daddy!

55
00:05:59,525 --> 00:06:01,444
- Where's your mom?
- Out shoppin'.

56
00:06:02,528 --> 00:06:04,864
- You're bleedin', Dad.
- Listen to me, John.

57
00:06:04,864 --> 00:06:07,074
This money here-- We gotta hide it
before they get to me.

58
00:06:07,116 --> 00:06:09,327
There's close to $10,000.
Where?

59
00:06:09,368 --> 00:06:11,954
Under a rock in the smokehouse? No.

60
00:06:11,954 --> 00:06:15,500
In the bricks in the grape harbor.
No, they'd dig for it.

61
00:06:16,626 --> 00:06:19,754
Sure. That's the place.

62
00:06:25,259 --> 00:06:27,303
- That's him.
- He probably still has that gun.

63
00:06:27,303 --> 00:06:31,057
Listen to me, son. You've gotta swear.
Swear means promise.

64
00:06:31,015 --> 00:06:34,227
First, swear you'll take care of little
Pearl, guard her with your lif e, boy.

65
00:06:34,185 --> 00:06:37,063
Then, swear you won't never tell where
the money's hid, not even your mom.

66
00:06:37,104 --> 00:06:38,814
- Yes, Dad.
- You understand?

67
00:06:38,814 --> 00:06:41,484
- Not even her?
- You've got common sense. She ain't.

68
00:06:41,442 --> 00:06:43,611
When you grow up,
that money will belong to you.

69
00:06:43,611 --> 00:06:46,531
Now stand up straight, look me
in the eye and raise your right hand.

70
00:06:46,489 --> 00:06:48,783
Now swear,
"I'll guard Pearl with my lif e."

71
00:06:48,824 --> 00:06:50,952
I will guard Pearl with my lif e.

72
00:06:50,952 --> 00:06:52,954
"And I won't never
tell about the money."

73
00:06:52,954 --> 00:06:55,957
And I won't never tell
about the money.

74
00:06:55,957 --> 00:06:58,167
You, Pearl, you swear too.

75
00:07:01,379 --> 00:07:02,630
Ben Harper.

76
00:07:04,131 --> 00:07:06,717
I'm going now, children.
Good-bye.

77
00:07:06,717 --> 00:07:09,178
Drop that gun, Harper.
We don't want the kids hurt.

78
00:07:09,220 --> 00:07:12,306
Just mind what you swore, son.
Mind, boy.

79
00:07:15,434 --> 00:07:18,980
Don't. Don't!

80
00:07:21,357 --> 00:07:22,441
Dad.

81
00:07:43,629 --> 00:07:47,049
Ben Harper, it is the sentence
of this court...

82
00:07:47,049 --> 00:07:50,136
that for the murder
of Ed Smiley and Corey South...

83
00:07:50,136 --> 00:07:53,055
you be hanged by the neck
until you are dead.

84
00:07:53,055 --> 00:07:55,683
And may God have mercy
on your soul.

85
00:08:09,822 --> 00:08:12,742
- It's mine.
- Where, Ben? Where?

86
00:08:15,536 --> 00:08:18,456
"And the little child
shall lead them."

87
00:08:18,414 --> 00:08:20,958
Come on, boy. Tell me.

88
00:08:24,545 --> 00:08:27,590
Ben, I'm a man of God.

89
00:08:27,548 --> 00:08:30,635
Trying to make me talk about it
in my sleep.

90
00:08:30,593 --> 00:08:32,887
What'd I say? What? What?

91
00:08:32,887 --> 00:08:34,889
You was quotin'
the scripture, Ben.

92
00:08:34,889 --> 00:08:38,017
You said, "And the little child
shall lead them."

93
00:08:45,858 --> 00:08:49,820
- You killed two men, Ben Harper.
- That's right, preacher.

94
00:08:49,779 --> 00:08:52,073
I robbed that bank
'cause I got tired of seein'...

95
00:08:53,282 --> 00:08:56,410
children roamin' the woodlands
without food--

96
00:08:56,410 --> 00:09:00,623
children roamin' the highways
in this era of depression--

97
00:09:00,581 --> 00:09:04,335
children sleepin' in old abandoned
car bodies and junk heaps.

98
00:09:04,293 --> 00:09:07,839
I promised myself I'd never see the day
when my young 'uns would want.

99
00:09:07,797 --> 00:09:10,258
With that $10,000,
I could build a tabernacle...

100
00:09:10,299 --> 00:09:13,636
make that Wheeling Tabernacle
look like a chicken house.

101
00:09:13,553 --> 00:09:16,013
Would you have free candy
for the kids, preacher?

102
00:09:16,013 --> 00:09:19,392
Think of it, Ben.
With that cursed, bloody gold.

103
00:09:19,350 --> 00:09:23,020
How come you got that stick knif e
hid up in your bed blankets, preacher?

104
00:09:22,979 --> 00:09:26,899
The Lord blinded mine enemies when
they brought me into this evil place.

105
00:09:26,816 --> 00:09:30,152
I smuggled it in right
under the noses of them guards.

106
00:09:31,320 --> 00:09:35,283
I come not with peace,
but with a sword.

107
00:09:35,241 --> 00:09:37,451
You, preacher?

108
00:09:37,493 --> 00:09:41,164
This sword has served me through
many an evil time, Ben Harper.

109
00:09:45,126 --> 00:09:47,795
What religion
do you prof ess, preacher?

110
00:09:47,795 --> 00:09:52,133
The religion the Almighty and me
worked out betwixt us.

111
00:09:52,091 --> 00:09:54,051
I'll bet.

112
00:09:56,804 --> 00:09:59,891
Salvation is a last-minute
business, boy.

113
00:09:59,891 --> 00:10:02,143
Keep talkin', preacher.

114
00:10:02,185 --> 00:10:05,938
If you let that money serve the Lord's
purpose, He might f eel kind towards you.

115
00:10:05,855 --> 00:10:07,315
Keep talkin', preacher.

116
00:10:07,356 --> 00:10:11,110
Now, don't you think the Lord
might change His mind if you was to--

117
00:10:21,579 --> 00:10:26,918
Lord, You sure knowed
what you was doing...

118
00:10:26,792 --> 00:10:31,923
when You put me in this very cell
at this very time.

119
00:10:31,797 --> 00:10:35,635
A man with $10,000 hidden somewhere...

120
00:10:35,551 --> 00:10:38,304
and a widow in the making.

121
00:10:54,862 --> 00:10:56,405
- Any trouble?
- No.

122
00:10:56,447 --> 00:10:58,950
He was a cool one, that Harper.
Never broke.

123
00:10:58,991 --> 00:11:01,077
Carried on some, kicked.

124
00:11:01,077 --> 00:11:03,246
They say he left a wif e
and two kids.

125
00:11:03,287 --> 00:11:05,289
I never heard.

126
00:11:07,041 --> 00:11:09,210
- He never told about the money?
- No.

127
00:11:09,210 --> 00:11:11,671
What do you figure
he done with it?

128
00:11:11,671 --> 00:11:14,590
He took the secret with him
when I dropped him.

129
00:11:17,593 --> 00:11:20,304
That you, Bart?
Supper's waitin'.

130
00:11:34,110 --> 00:11:38,739
Mother, sometimes I think it might be
better if I was to quit my job as guard.

131
00:11:38,614 --> 00:11:43,327
You're always this way after a hanging.
You never have to be there.

132
00:11:45,454 --> 00:11:47,832
Sometimes I wish
I was back in the mine.

133
00:11:47,874 --> 00:11:51,460
And leave me a widow after
another blast like the one in '24?

134
00:11:51,377 --> 00:11:53,796
Not on your lif e, old mister.

135
00:12:12,356 --> 00:12:17,153
Hing, hang, hung
See what the hangman done

136
00:12:17,111 --> 00:12:20,198
Hing, hang, hing, hang
Hing, hang, hung

137
00:12:20,990 --> 00:12:23,075
See what the hangman done

138
00:12:23,075 --> 00:12:27,330
Hung, hang, hing
See the robber swing

139
00:12:27,288 --> 00:12:30,958
Hing, hang, hing, hang
Hing, hang, hing, hang

140
00:12:30,917 --> 00:12:35,004
Hing, hang, hung
Now my song is done

141
00:12:34,962 --> 00:12:38,758
Hing, hang, hung
See what the hangman done

142
00:12:38,716 --> 00:12:42,762
Hung, hang, hing
See the robber swing

143
00:12:57,276 --> 00:12:59,445
Are you going to buy it, John?

144
00:12:59,445 --> 00:13:04,033
Oh, so your mommy's keeping you
out of school these days.

145
00:13:03,950 --> 00:13:06,869
How is your poor, poor mother?

146
00:13:06,827 --> 00:13:08,996
She's at Spoon's Ice Cream Parlor.

147
00:13:08,996 --> 00:13:13,417
Did they ever find out what your father
done with all that money he stole?

148
00:13:16,212 --> 00:13:18,631
Pearl and me,
we have to go.

149
00:13:24,637 --> 00:13:26,889
- You better not sing that song.
- Why?

150
00:13:26,931 --> 00:13:29,267
'Cause you're too little.

151
00:13:30,351 --> 00:13:32,144
Can we get some candy?

152
00:13:39,944 --> 00:13:42,864
Willa Harper, there are certain
plain facts of lif e that adds up...

153
00:13:42,822 --> 00:13:45,867
just like two plus two makes four,
and one of them is this--

154
00:13:45,825 --> 00:13:48,786
No woman is able to raise
growing youngsters alone.

155
00:13:48,744 --> 00:13:50,997
The Lord meant that job for two.

156
00:13:50,997 --> 00:13:53,875
Icey, I just don't want a husband.

157
00:14:01,799 --> 00:14:03,801
It ain't a question
of wanting or not wanting.

158
00:14:03,843 --> 00:14:06,679
You're no spring chicken.
You're a grown woman with two children.

159
00:14:06,637 --> 00:14:09,390
It's a man you need
in the house, Willa Harper.

160
00:14:22,612 --> 00:14:24,947
Tell me a story, John.

161
00:14:26,657 --> 00:14:30,203
Well, once upon a time...

162
00:14:30,161 --> 00:14:34,832
there was a rich king who had himself
a son and a daughter.

163
00:14:37,293 --> 00:14:40,379
They all lived in a castle
over in Africa.

164
00:14:43,925 --> 00:14:48,888
And one day, this king
got taken away by some bad men.

165
00:14:48,763 --> 00:14:51,307
And before he got took off...

166
00:14:51,349 --> 00:14:55,311
he told his son to kill anyone
who tried to steal his gold.

167
00:14:57,104 --> 00:15:00,149
And before long,
the bad men came back and--

168
00:15:15,414 --> 00:15:18,751
Leaning

169
00:15:20,253 --> 00:15:23,172
Just a man.
Good night, Pearl.

170
00:15:23,130 --> 00:15:26,217
Sleep tight
and don't let the bedbugs bite.

171
00:15:26,175 --> 00:15:29,095
Good night, Miss Jenny.
Don't let the bedbugs bite.

172
00:15:30,179 --> 00:15:33,766
Leaning

173
00:15:37,436 --> 00:15:44,694
Leaning on the everlasting Arm

174
00:16:24,901 --> 00:16:29,238
She don't put in here no more,
but she still blows as she passes.

175
00:16:34,076 --> 00:16:36,370
Come on in and have
a cup of coff ee, boy.

176
00:16:36,329 --> 00:16:39,207
Ain't nobody stole Dad's skiff.

177
00:16:39,207 --> 00:16:43,085
Ain't nobody gonna, neither,
long as Uncle Birdie's around.

178
00:16:45,004 --> 00:16:49,383
First day my joints is limberin' up,
I'll go and give her a good caulkin'.

179
00:16:51,719 --> 00:16:53,971
Ain't seen ya
in a coon's age, boy.

180
00:16:53,971 --> 00:16:57,517
- I've been mindin' Pearl.
- Shucks, ain't it a caution...

181
00:16:57,517 --> 00:17:00,937
what a woman will load
onto a man's back when he ain't lookin'?

182
00:17:13,991 --> 00:17:16,911
Excuse me, Cap,
while I sweeten' my coff ee.

183
00:17:27,964 --> 00:17:31,425
Dead and gone these 25 years,
and never takes her eyes off me.

184
00:17:34,762 --> 00:17:38,850
A man of my years needs a little snort
in the mornin', heat the boilers.

185
00:17:40,017 --> 00:17:41,644
Yeah.

186
00:17:41,686 --> 00:17:44,689
I was talkin' to this stranger
up at the boardin' house.

187
00:17:44,647 --> 00:17:47,817
- He knowed your dad.
- Where did he know Dad?

188
00:17:47,775 --> 00:17:51,362
I'll not hide it from you, boy. He
knowed in the Moundsville Penitentiary.

189
00:17:51,362 --> 00:17:56,075
- I gotta go now, Uncle Birdie.
- Well, you just got here, boy.

190
00:17:58,244 --> 00:18:01,330
I told Mom I'd be back
to Spoon's for Pearl.

191
00:18:23,227 --> 00:18:27,231
God works in a mysterious way,
His wonders to perform.

192
00:18:27,190 --> 00:18:29,483
Yes, I was with Brother Harper
right up to the end.

193
00:18:30,902 --> 00:18:33,404
Now that I'm no longer employed
by the penitentiary...

194
00:18:33,404 --> 00:18:36,157
it is my joy to bring
this small comfort to his loved ones.

195
00:18:36,157 --> 00:18:38,826
It's a mighty good man
would go out of his way...

196
00:18:38,826 --> 00:18:41,829
to bring a word of cheer
to a grievin' widow.

197
00:18:41,787 --> 00:18:46,209
- So you ain't with the state no more?
- No, brother, I resigned yesterday.

198
00:18:46,125 --> 00:18:49,754
The heartrendin' spectacle of them
poor men was just too much for me.

199
00:18:50,796 --> 00:18:53,466
Ah, little lad,
you're starin' at my fingers.

200
00:18:53,424 --> 00:18:57,220
Would you like me to tell you the little
story of "Right Hand, Left Hand--"

201
00:18:57,178 --> 00:18:59,305
the story of good and evil?

202
00:19:00,264 --> 00:19:02,391
"H-A-T-E."

203
00:19:02,433 --> 00:19:04,727
It was with this left hand
that old Brother Cain...

204
00:19:04,685 --> 00:19:07,355
struck the blow
that laid his brother low.

205
00:19:07,396 --> 00:19:11,484
"L-O-V-E."
You see these fingers, dear hearts?

206
00:19:11,400 --> 00:19:14,487
These fingers has veins that run
straight to the soul of man.

207
00:19:14,487 --> 00:19:17,448
The right hand, friends.
The hand of love.

208
00:19:17,406 --> 00:19:19,534
Now watch, and I'll show you
the story of lif e.

209
00:19:20,326 --> 00:19:24,705
These fingers is always a-warrin'
and a-tuggin' one again' the other.

210
00:19:25,623 --> 00:19:27,625
Now watch 'em.

211
00:19:27,625 --> 00:19:31,754
Old Brother Left Hand.
Left Hand hates a-fightin'.

212
00:19:31,671 --> 00:19:34,131
It looks like Love's a goner.

213
00:19:34,090 --> 00:19:37,385
But wait a minute.
Wait a minute!

214
00:19:37,385 --> 00:19:41,889
Love's a-winnin'.
Yes, sirree.

215
00:19:41,806 --> 00:19:43,975
It's Love that won...

216
00:19:43,933 --> 00:19:47,478
and old Left Hand Hate
is down for the count!

217
00:19:49,146 --> 00:19:51,983
I never heard it better told.

218
00:19:51,941 --> 00:19:56,112
I wish every soul in this community
could get the benefit.

219
00:19:56,904 --> 00:20:00,241
Oh, you've just got to stay
for our picnic Sunday.

220
00:20:00,241 --> 00:20:03,536
No, I must wend my way downriver
on the Lord's business.

221
00:20:03,494 --> 00:20:06,289
You ain't leavin' in no hurry
if we can help it.

222
00:20:06,247 --> 00:20:10,334
John, mind your manners.
Take that look off your face. Act nice.

223
00:20:11,169 --> 00:20:13,754
Why, he don't mean
no impudence, do you, boy?

224
00:20:13,754 --> 00:20:15,548
Do you, boy?

225
00:20:16,507 --> 00:20:19,594
Many's the time poor Brother Ben
told me about these young 'uns.

226
00:20:19,552 --> 00:20:21,095
What'd he tell you?

227
00:20:21,137 --> 00:20:24,765
Why, he told me what fine little lambs
you and your sister both was.

228
00:20:24,765 --> 00:20:26,309
Is that all?

229
00:20:26,350 --> 00:20:30,688
Why, no, boy.
He told me lots and lots of things.

230
00:20:30,605 --> 00:20:33,691
- Nice things, boy.
- Thank you.

231
00:20:36,611 --> 00:20:38,654
My, that fudge smells yummy.

232
00:20:39,614 --> 00:20:41,699
It's for the picnic.

233
00:20:41,699 --> 00:20:46,704
And you don't get a smidgen of my fudge
unless you stay for the picnic.

