244
00:21:30,998 --> 00:21:33,960
Don't he have the grandest
singin' voice?

245
00:21:33,960 --> 00:21:36,963
John, Pearl,
run along and play, you two.

246
00:21:36,963 --> 00:21:39,257
- Where?
- Down by the river. My goodness!

247
00:21:41,384 --> 00:21:44,220
That f ella's just achin' to settle down
with some nice woman...

248
00:21:44,220 --> 00:21:46,305
and make a home for himself.

249
00:21:46,347 --> 00:21:48,933
Icey, it's awful soon
after Ben's passing.

250
00:21:48,933 --> 00:21:53,563
- If ever I saw a sign from heaven.
- John don't like him much.

251
00:21:53,521 --> 00:21:56,983
- Pearl dotes on him.
- The boy worries me.

252
00:21:57,817 --> 00:22:01,737
I know it's silly, but it's like there's
something still between him and his dad.

253
00:22:01,696 --> 00:22:04,323
What he needs
is a dose of sauce.

254
00:22:04,365 --> 00:22:07,285
- No, there's somethin' else.
- What?

255
00:22:07,243 --> 00:22:09,954
- The money.
- I declare, Willa Harper...

256
00:22:09,954 --> 00:22:12,790
you'll let that money haunt you
to your grave.

257
00:22:12,790 --> 00:22:14,834
Icey, I would
love to be satisfied...

258
00:22:14,876 --> 00:22:17,753
that Harry Powell don't think I got
that money hid somewhere.

259
00:22:17,753 --> 00:22:20,965
You come right out
and ask that man of God.

260
00:22:20,965 --> 00:22:25,261
Mr. Powell! Clear that evil mud
out of your soul.

261
00:22:25,136 --> 00:22:29,098
John! Pearl! Come along here,
get some fudge.

262
00:22:29,056 --> 00:22:31,684
- I don't want no fudge.
- You do what you're told!

263
00:22:31,726 --> 00:22:35,062
- You go sit down by the river.
- Oh, Icey, I'm a sight.

264
00:22:35,021 --> 00:22:37,064
Get along with you.

265
00:22:41,944 --> 00:22:43,404
You!

266
00:22:45,573 --> 00:22:48,451
That young lady better look sharp,
or some smart sister...

267
00:22:48,451 --> 00:22:51,120
is gonna snap him up
right from under her nose.

268
00:22:51,120 --> 00:22:53,247
She's not the only fish
in the river.

269
00:22:53,289 --> 00:22:56,667
Now, you two stay put.
Shilly-shallying around.

270
00:22:56,626 --> 00:22:58,961
A husband's one piece of store goods
you never know...

271
00:22:59,003 --> 00:23:01,255
till you get it home
and take the paper off.

272
00:23:01,255 --> 00:23:06,219
Did Ben Harper ever tell you
what he done with the money he stole?

273
00:23:06,093 --> 00:23:09,305
My dear child, don't you know?

274
00:23:10,473 --> 00:23:12,808
She's moanin' about Ben Harper.

275
00:23:12,808 --> 00:23:15,561
That wasn't love.
That was just flapdoodle.

276
00:23:15,561 --> 00:23:17,522
Have some fudge, lambs.

277
00:23:17,563 --> 00:23:19,565
When you've been married
to a man for 40 years...

278
00:23:19,607 --> 00:23:22,318
you know all that don't amount
to a hill of beans.

279
00:23:22,276 --> 00:23:26,239
I've been married to my Walt that long,
and I swear in all that time...

280
00:23:26,197 --> 00:23:29,367
I just lie there
thinkin' about my canning.

281
00:23:45,967 --> 00:23:49,512
A woman's a fool to marry for that.
That's somethin' for a man.

282
00:23:49,428 --> 00:23:52,348
The Good Lord never meant
for a decent woman to want that.

283
00:23:52,348 --> 00:23:54,559
Not really want it.

284
00:23:54,600 --> 00:23:57,520
It's all just a fake
and a pipe dream.

285
00:23:59,397 --> 00:24:02,358
John, Mr. Powell
has something to tell you.

286
00:24:04,986 --> 00:24:09,740
Well, John, the night before
your father died...

287
00:24:09,657 --> 00:24:13,244
he told me what he did
with that money.

288
00:24:13,244 --> 00:24:15,830
That money's
at the bottom of the river...

289
00:24:15,830 --> 00:24:19,458
wrapped around
a 12-pound cobblestone.

290
00:24:20,376 --> 00:24:22,128
Thank you, Harry.

291
00:24:23,713 --> 00:24:25,882
I f eel clean now.

292
00:24:25,923 --> 00:24:29,218
My whole body's
just a-quiverin' with cleanness.

293
00:24:33,890 --> 00:24:36,017
John, come here.

294
00:24:36,017 --> 00:24:38,186
Your tie is crooked.

295
00:24:52,575 --> 00:24:55,953
Along the river shore

296
00:24:55,953 --> 00:24:59,582
Birdie Steptoe was a pilot

297
00:24:59,540 --> 00:25:02,585
In the good ol' days of yore

298
00:25:02,585 --> 00:25:07,131
Now he sets in his ol' wharf boat

299
00:25:07,089 --> 00:25:09,926
All the big boats heave a sigh

300
00:25:09,884 --> 00:25:13,095
- When will Dad's skiff be ready?
- Can't hear you, boy.

301
00:25:13,095 --> 00:25:17,934
They blow for Uncle Birdie and

302
00:25:17,808 --> 00:25:22,480
The times that ere gone by

303
00:25:22,396 --> 00:25:24,398
When will the skiff be ready?

304
00:25:24,398 --> 00:25:27,610
Have her ready inside a week,
and then we'll go fishin'.

305
00:25:27,568 --> 00:25:31,155
- How's your ma?
- Oh, she's all right.

306
00:25:31,113 --> 00:25:33,282
- How's your sister Pearl?
- Just fine.

307
00:25:33,324 --> 00:25:36,494
- You leavin', boy?
- Yep. Gotta watch out for Pearl.

308
00:25:36,452 --> 00:25:39,372
Well, good night, boy.
Come again anytime.

309
00:25:40,373 --> 00:25:44,335
And mind, boy, I'll have your pa's skiff
shipshape inside a week.

310
00:26:13,990 --> 00:26:15,950
Is somebody there?

311
00:26:26,085 --> 00:26:28,045
Anybody there?

312
00:26:31,340 --> 00:26:33,301
Anybody here?

313
00:26:33,342 --> 00:26:35,511
Good evenin', John.

314
00:26:37,471 --> 00:26:40,558
I had a little talk
with your mother tonight, John...

315
00:26:40,516 --> 00:26:45,938
and your mother decided it might be best
for me to let you know the news.

316
00:26:45,855 --> 00:26:50,776
Your mother told me she wanted me
to be a daddy to you and your sister.

317
00:26:50,693 --> 00:26:52,820
We're gonna get married, boy.

318
00:26:54,530 --> 00:26:58,993
Did you hear what I said, boy?
Married.

319
00:26:59,619 --> 00:27:02,997
We're going to Sisterville tomorrow,
and when we get back--

320
00:27:02,914 --> 00:27:06,667
You ain't my dad.
You'll never be my dad.

321
00:27:06,626 --> 00:27:10,379
When we get back,
we're all going to be friends...

322
00:27:10,379 --> 00:27:13,299
and share our fortunes
together, John.

323
00:27:13,299 --> 00:27:16,802
You think you can make me tell,
but I won't, I won't, I won't!

324
00:27:19,805 --> 00:27:23,267
- Tell me what, boy?
- Nothin'.

325
00:27:23,226 --> 00:27:26,812
We're not keeping secrets
from each other, are we, little lad?

326
00:27:30,775 --> 00:27:35,696
Well, no matter.
We've got a long time together, boy.

327
00:27:42,495 --> 00:27:45,873
Raise your hand! Great sakes!

328
00:27:45,790 --> 00:27:48,835
Now you wait here
while I get your night things.

329
00:27:53,923 --> 00:27:56,592
- Now can I tell?
- Hmm?

330
00:27:56,592 --> 00:27:59,971
Mr. Powell's our daddy now.
Can I tell him about--

331
00:27:59,929 --> 00:28:01,931
- You swore, Pearl.
- John, don't.

332
00:28:01,973 --> 00:28:04,058
You promised Dad
you wouldn't tell.

333
00:28:04,100 --> 00:28:07,603
I love Mr. Powell
lots and lots, John.

334
00:28:38,509 --> 00:28:40,011
Men.

335
00:28:57,236 --> 00:28:59,238
Fix that window shade.

336
00:29:10,416 --> 00:29:13,336
I was praying.

337
00:29:13,336 --> 00:29:17,798
I'm sorry. I didn't know.
I thought--

338
00:29:17,715 --> 00:29:20,635
You thought, Willa, that
the moment you walked in that door...

339
00:29:20,635 --> 00:29:23,763
I'd start to pawin' you
in that abominable way...

340
00:29:23,763 --> 00:29:26,641
that men are supposed to do
on their weddin' night.

341
00:29:26,599 --> 00:29:28,518
Ain't that right?

342
00:29:30,853 --> 00:29:34,023
I think it's time we made on thing
perf ectly clear, Willa.

343
00:29:34,023 --> 00:29:38,402
Marriage, to me, represents a blending
of two spirits in the sight of heaven.

344
00:29:50,540 --> 00:29:52,041
Get up, Willa.

345
00:29:54,418 --> 00:29:57,463
- Harry, what--
- Get up.

346
00:30:00,132 --> 00:30:03,135
Now go look at yourself
yonder in that mirror.

347
00:30:04,971 --> 00:30:06,931
Do as I say.

348
00:30:19,902 --> 00:30:21,904
Look at yourself.

349
00:30:24,115 --> 00:30:26,868
What do you see, girl?

350
00:30:26,826 --> 00:30:32,081
You see the body of a woman,
a temple of creation and motherhood.

351
00:30:31,998 --> 00:30:36,169
You see the flesh of Eve
that man since Adam has profaned.

352
00:30:36,127 --> 00:30:38,546
That body was meant
for begettin' children.

353
00:30:38,546 --> 00:30:41,883
It was not meant
for the lust of men.

354
00:30:43,467 --> 00:30:46,429
Do you want more children, Willa?

355
00:30:48,806 --> 00:30:52,268
It's the business of this marriage
to mind those two you have now...

356
00:30:52,226 --> 00:30:54,187
not to beget more.

357
00:30:54,228 --> 00:30:55,688
Yes.

358
00:31:03,404 --> 00:31:07,200
All right, you can get in bed now
and stop shiverin'.

359
00:31:09,327 --> 00:31:11,537
Help me to get clean...

360
00:31:11,579 --> 00:31:14,749
so I can be
what Harry wants me to be.

361
00:31:22,131 --> 00:31:25,301
Meanest, orneriest, sneakiest critter
in the whole river, boy.

362
00:31:25,301 --> 00:31:26,761
The gar.

363
00:31:28,221 --> 00:31:31,265
- Here's your can of hooks.
- P'shaw, boy.

364
00:31:31,224 --> 00:31:34,810
Ain't a hook in the land
strong enough to land Mr. Gar.

365
00:31:34,769 --> 00:31:39,190
What a f ellow needs
is a mother wit and a horsehair.

366
00:31:39,106 --> 00:31:41,692
Golly, won't it bust it,
Uncle Birdie?

367
00:31:41,692 --> 00:31:45,071
No, horsehair'll hold
a lumpin' whale.

368
00:31:45,029 --> 00:31:47,573
- You mind my cussin', boy?
- No.

369
00:31:47,615 --> 00:31:51,577
Well, the reason I ask--
Your step-pa bein' a preacher and all.

370
00:31:54,747 --> 00:31:58,459
Never was much of a one
for preachin' myself.

371
00:31:58,417 --> 00:32:00,545
I don't know what's wrong
up at your house...

372
00:32:00,545 --> 00:32:03,256
but always remember, cap...

373
00:32:03,256 --> 00:32:06,801
if you're ever in trouble,
holler and come a-runnin'.

374
00:32:06,759 --> 00:32:09,011
Uncle Birdie's your friend.

375
00:32:13,933 --> 00:32:19,146
There! You slimy, snag-toothed,
bait-stealin' so-and-so!

376
00:32:20,273 --> 00:32:22,066
Amen!

377
00:32:22,108 --> 00:32:24,777
You have all sinned!

378
00:32:24,819 --> 00:32:29,031
Which one of you can say,
as I can say...

379
00:32:28,948 --> 00:32:31,826
that you drove a good man
to murder?

380
00:32:31,868 --> 00:32:34,203
Because I kept a-houndin' him...

381
00:32:34,162 --> 00:32:37,748
for perfume and clothes
and face paint.

382
00:32:37,748 --> 00:32:42,211
And he slew two human beings...

383
00:32:42,128 --> 00:32:45,298
and he come to me and he said...

384
00:32:45,298 --> 00:32:50,428
"Take this money and buy yourself
the clothes and the paint."

385
00:32:51,429 --> 00:32:54,432
But brethren, brethren...

386
00:32:54,390 --> 00:32:57,185
that's where the Lord stepped in.

387
00:32:59,645 --> 00:33:00,771
Yes!

388
00:33:02,648 --> 00:33:06,027
He said, the Lord to that man...

389
00:33:05,985 --> 00:33:11,324
"You take that money
and you throw it in the river."

390
00:33:11,199 --> 00:33:15,161
- In the river!
- In the river!

391
00:33:37,558 --> 00:33:40,478
Now, you're John and you're Pearl.

392
00:33:42,355 --> 00:33:46,943
You'll get awful mad, John.
I done a sin.

393
00:33:46,901 --> 00:33:49,570
I didn't tell no one.

394
00:33:53,950 --> 00:33:55,827
It's all here.

395
00:34:14,512 --> 00:34:17,557
- Oh, yes?
- What are you doing, boy?

396
00:34:17,557 --> 00:34:21,352
- Gettin' Pearl to bed.
- What's takin' you so long about it?

397
00:34:21,352 --> 00:34:22,812
Nothing.

398
00:34:28,401 --> 00:34:31,946
- What's that you're playin' with?
- Pearl's junk.

399
00:34:31,904 --> 00:34:35,283
Mom gets mad when she plays out here
and don't put it away.

400
00:34:35,241 --> 00:34:37,201
Come on, children.

401
00:34:40,872 --> 00:34:43,207
Off to bed with the both of you.

402
00:34:49,505 --> 00:34:51,507
Come here, John.

403
00:34:54,468 --> 00:34:57,054
Your mother tells me
you tattled on me.

404
00:34:57,054 --> 00:34:59,682
She said you told her
I asked where that money was hid.

405
00:35:02,143 --> 00:35:04,645
That wasn't very nice, boy.

406
00:35:04,604 --> 00:35:07,106
- Have a heart.
- Yeah.

407
00:35:08,566 --> 00:35:12,528
Well, it doesn't matter.
It's your word against mine.

408
00:35:12,487 --> 00:35:14,614
It's me your mother believes.

409
00:35:19,994 --> 00:35:22,955
Were you impudent again
to Mr. Powell, John?

410
00:35:22,914 --> 00:35:25,249
Mom, I didn't mean it.

411
00:35:26,417 --> 00:35:28,920
What were you impudent about?

412
00:35:28,920 --> 00:35:32,173
He asked me
about the money again, Mom.

413
00:35:32,173 --> 00:35:36,844
John, you always make up that lie.
There is no money.

414
00:35:36,761 --> 00:35:39,972
Why can't you get that
through your head?

415
00:35:39,931 --> 00:35:42,808
That boy's as stubborn
and as mulish as a sheep.

416
00:35:42,767 --> 00:35:44,977
- It's a shame.
- Good night, Icey.

417
00:35:44,977 --> 00:35:47,104
- Good night, honey.
- Good night, Walt.

418
00:35:47,104 --> 00:35:48,397
Good night, Willa.

419
00:35:50,525 --> 00:35:52,944
Plan on a longer visit next time.

420
00:35:52,944 --> 00:35:55,863
You hardly get settled before
you're frettin' to get home again.

421
00:35:55,822 --> 00:35:58,616
I'm needed to keep peace
and harmony betwixt them.

422
00:35:58,616 --> 00:36:01,536
It's my burden,
and I'm proud of it, Icey.

423
00:36:11,420 --> 00:36:15,132
- Where is the money hid?
- I don't know.

424
00:36:15,091 --> 00:36:18,010
She thinks that money's
at the bottom of the river.

425
00:36:17,969 --> 00:36:20,596
But you and me, we know better,
don't we, little lad?

426
00:36:20,596 --> 00:36:22,723
I don't know nothin'.

427
00:36:22,723 --> 00:36:26,435
Well, never mind, boy.
Summer's young yet.

428
00:36:28,646 --> 00:36:30,106
Come here.

429
00:36:33,401 --> 00:36:35,486
John's a f ellow
that likes to keep secrets.

430
00:36:35,528 --> 00:36:38,072
- I'll tell you a secret.
- Yes?

431
00:36:38,114 --> 00:36:40,741
I knowed your daddy.

432
00:36:40,741 --> 00:36:43,828
And do you know
what your daddy told me?

433
00:36:43,828 --> 00:36:46,038
He said,
"You tell my little girl Pearl...

434
00:36:46,038 --> 00:36:48,875
that there's to be no secrets
between her and you."

435
00:36:48,916 --> 00:36:52,587
- Yes.
- All right, now it's your turn.

436
00:36:52,545 --> 00:36:54,505
What secret shall I tell?

437
00:36:54,547 --> 00:36:57,216
Oh, uh, what's your name?

438
00:36:58,801 --> 00:37:01,512
You're just foolin'.
My name's Pearl.

439
00:37:03,472 --> 00:37:08,186
Well, I reckon I'll have to try again.
Where's the money hid?

440
00:37:10,605 --> 00:37:14,192
Pearl, you swore you wouldn't tell!
You swore! You swore!

441
00:37:14,192 --> 00:37:17,028
You hit Daddy with a hairbrush.

442
00:37:18,946 --> 00:37:22,575
Now, you see, we just can't have
anything to do with John.

443
00:37:22,533 --> 00:37:25,036
You and me'll go on down
to the parlor, Pearl.

444
00:37:43,012 --> 00:37:45,973
John is just plumb bad,
through and through.

445
00:37:45,932 --> 00:37:49,143
- John's bad.
- Yes, John's bad.

446
00:37:50,144 --> 00:37:52,730
Tell me another secret
about my dad.

447
00:37:52,730 --> 00:37:54,649
Oh, no. Your turn.

448
00:37:54,690 --> 00:37:58,069
Well, like,
what secret shall I tell?

449
00:37:58,069 --> 00:38:00,571
Where's the money hid?

450
00:38:00,530 --> 00:38:03,658
- John's bad.
- Where's the money hid?

451
00:38:03,658 --> 00:38:07,578
Tell me, you little wretch,
or I'll tear your arm off!

452
00:38:19,841 --> 00:38:23,553
- Icey, I'm worried about Willa.
- How do you mean?

453
00:38:23,511 --> 00:38:26,347
Well, I'm figurin' how to say it
so as you won't get mad.

454
00:38:26,347 --> 00:38:28,432
Say what, Walt Spoon?

455
00:38:28,474 --> 00:38:30,685
- There's somethin' wrong about it.
- About what?

456
00:38:30,685 --> 00:38:33,604
About Mr. Powell.
All of it.

457
00:38:33,563 --> 00:38:35,857
Now, Mother, a body's
got a right to their f eelings.

458
00:38:35,898 --> 00:38:39,277
May the Lord have mercy on you,
Walt Spoon.

459
00:38:39,277 --> 00:38:40,570
Mother, I was just--

460
00:38:44,657 --> 00:38:46,117
Amen.

461
00:38:47,994 --> 00:38:52,665
- Are you through praying?
- I'm through, Harry.

462
00:38:52,540 --> 00:38:55,293
You were listening
outside the parlor window.

463
00:38:55,251 --> 00:38:58,754
- It ain't in the river, is it, Harry?
- Answer me!

464
00:38:58,713 --> 00:39:02,675
Ben never told you
he throwed it in the river, did he?

465
00:39:12,560 --> 00:39:14,896
The children know where it's hid.

466
00:39:14,937 --> 00:39:17,690
John knows.
Is that it, Harry?

467
00:39:22,528 --> 00:39:25,865
Then it's still here
amongst us...

468
00:39:25,865 --> 00:39:28,326
tainting us.

469
00:39:30,870 --> 00:39:34,207
You must've known about it
all along, Harry.

470
00:39:34,165 --> 00:39:38,002
But that ain't the reason
why you married me.

471
00:39:37,960 --> 00:39:40,004
I know that much.

472
00:39:41,547 --> 00:39:45,218
Because the Lord
just wouldn't let it be.

473
00:39:45,176 --> 00:39:48,179
He made you marry me...

474
00:39:48,137 --> 00:39:53,100
so you could show me
the way and the lif e...

475
00:39:53,017 --> 00:39:55,561
and the salvation of my soul.

476
00:39:57,355 --> 00:39:59,941
Ain't that so, Harry.

477
00:39:59,899 --> 00:40:03,861
So you might say that it was the money
that brung us together.

478
00:40:05,446 --> 00:40:07,782
The rest of it don't matter.

479
00:41:05,339 --> 00:41:06,799
Walt, come quick!

480
00:41:06,883 --> 00:41:09,719
- What's wrong, Mother?
- Shhh! He's in there.

481
00:41:09,677 --> 00:41:11,137
- Who?
- Mr. Powell.

482
00:41:11,179 --> 00:41:14,348
Willa has run away.

483
00:41:14,348 --> 00:41:15,892
Just went?

484
00:41:15,892 --> 00:41:18,728
She took off some time in the night
in that old Model-T.

485
00:41:18,686 --> 00:41:21,189
- Oh, is he hit pretty bad?
- All to pieces.

486
00:41:21,189 --> 00:41:23,357
Well, there's a little
peach brandy in here--

487
00:41:23,399 --> 00:41:27,069
- A man of the cloth?
- Well, just a sip.

488
00:41:26,986 --> 00:41:30,364
Walt Spoon,
that's for sickness in the house!

489
00:41:31,449 --> 00:41:32,909
What can we do, Mother?

490
00:41:32,992 --> 00:41:35,119
I thought if you went
and talked to him.

491
00:41:35,161 --> 00:41:37,747
Now, Mother, please.
I'm no good--

492
00:41:40,791 --> 00:41:44,712
- Mr. Powell.
- A strange woman is a narrow pit.

493
00:41:44,629 --> 00:41:48,883
She lieth in wait as for pray and
increaseth the transgressors among men.

494
00:41:50,134 --> 00:41:53,137
My dear, dear friends,
whatever would I do without you?

495
00:41:53,095 --> 00:41:56,390
- Mr. Powell.
- Well, if there's anything--

496
00:41:56,390 --> 00:42:00,144
No, it's my shame, my crown of thorns.
I must wear it bravely.

497
00:42:00,102 --> 00:42:03,689
- What could have possessed that girl?
- Satan.

498
00:42:03,648 --> 00:42:05,358
Didn't you have no inkling?

499
00:42:06,025 --> 00:42:08,861
Yes I did,
from the very first night.

500
00:42:08,861 --> 00:42:11,697
- First night?
- Our honeymoon.

501
00:42:11,656 --> 00:42:13,783
How's that?

502
00:42:13,825 --> 00:42:16,285
She turned me out of the bed.

503
00:42:16,285 --> 00:42:18,579
No!

504
00:42:18,538 --> 00:42:20,915
Well, what do you figure to do?

505
00:42:20,915 --> 00:42:25,169
Do? Why, just stay right here
and take care of them kids.

506
00:42:25,086 --> 00:42:28,464
Maybe it was never meant for a woman
like Willa to taint their young lives.

507
00:42:30,091 --> 00:42:32,051
That's mighty brave of you, preacher.

508
00:42:32,093 --> 00:42:35,888
Oh, I reckon it was just
ordained that way, Brother Spoon.

509
00:42:35,847 --> 00:42:38,558
Didn't she leave no word?

510
00:42:39,475 --> 00:42:43,396
A scrawl, on a notepaper
on the bureau.

511
00:42:43,354 --> 00:42:45,356
I burned it.

512
00:42:45,356 --> 00:42:49,193
Tore it up and burned it,
it stank so strong of hellfire.

513
00:42:49,110 --> 00:42:51,028
Amen!

514
00:42:51,028 --> 00:42:54,365
The pitcher has went to the well
once too often, friends.

515
00:42:54,323 --> 00:42:56,993
Oh, she'll come
draggin' her tail back home.

516
00:42:56,993 --> 00:43:00,955
She'll not be back.
I reckon I'm saf e in promisin' you that.

517
00:43:00,913 --> 00:43:03,207
- Maybe she just run offon a spree.
- Oh, no.

518
00:43:03,207 --> 00:43:06,377
- Well, there's no harm in hoping.
- Ain't no sense in it, neither.

519
00:43:08,004 --> 00:43:11,257
I figured somethin' like that was
brewin' when she went to bed last night.

520
00:43:11,174 --> 00:43:12,300
How?

521
00:43:13,801 --> 00:43:16,762
Well, she tarried around in the kitchen
after I'd gone up.

522
00:43:16,762 --> 00:43:21,100
- When I went to see what was wrong--
- What?

523
00:43:21,017 --> 00:43:23,978
Well, she'd found this jar
of dandelion wine...

524
00:43:23,978 --> 00:43:27,565
that the husband, that Harper,
had hid somewhere in the cellar.

525
00:43:28,983 --> 00:43:30,985
She was drinkin'.

526
00:43:32,320 --> 00:43:35,740
- I tried to save her.
- I know you did, Mr. Powell.

527
00:43:35,698 --> 00:43:37,742
I know how hard you tried.

528
00:43:37,742 --> 00:43:40,703
But the Devil wins sometimes.

529
00:43:40,703 --> 00:43:44,207
Can't nobody say I didn't do
my best to save her.

530
00:44:43,266 --> 00:44:45,643
Leaning

531
00:44:48,354 --> 00:44:53,734
Saf e and secure from all alarm

532
00:44:53,609 --> 00:44:56,195
Leaning

533
00:44:58,656 --> 00:45:04,453
Leaning on the everlasting Arm

534
00:45:06,414 --> 00:45:08,124
Children!

535
00:45:28,394 --> 00:45:29,854
Careful.

536
00:45:31,355 --> 00:45:33,566
Why do we have to hide, John?

537
00:45:36,736 --> 00:45:39,155
- Where's Mom?
- She's gone to Moundsville.

538
00:45:39,197 --> 00:45:42,492
- To see Dad?
- Yes, I reckon that's it.

539
00:45:50,374 --> 00:45:53,461
Now, listen to me, Pearl.
You and me is runnin' off tonight.

540
00:45:53,461 --> 00:45:54,754
Why?

541
00:45:54,795 --> 00:45:58,382
If we stay here,
somethin' awful will happen to us.

542
00:45:58,299 --> 00:46:01,677
- Won't Daddy Powell take care of us?
- No.

543
00:46:01,636 --> 00:46:04,514
That's just it. No.

544
00:46:11,771 --> 00:46:14,732
- Where are we going, John?
- Somewhere. I don't know yet.

545
00:46:16,067 --> 00:46:19,237
- I'm hungry, John.
- We'll steal something to eat.

546
00:46:19,237 --> 00:46:21,614
It'll spoil our supper.

547
00:46:27,203 --> 00:46:30,289
I can hear you whisperin', children,
so I know you're down there.

548
00:46:30,289 --> 00:46:33,334
I can f eel myself gettin' awful mad.

549
00:46:36,879 --> 00:46:40,967
I'm out of patience, children.
I'm coming to find you now.

550
00:46:40,883 --> 00:46:44,762
Yoo-hoo! Mr. Powell!

551
00:46:48,933 --> 00:46:53,855
- Well, well, Mrs. Spoon.
- Where are the children?

552
00:46:53,813 --> 00:46:56,065
They're down there
in that cellar playin' games.

553
00:46:56,065 --> 00:47:00,194
They won't mind me when I call them.
I'm at my wit's end, Mrs. Spoon.

554
00:47:10,621 --> 00:47:12,665
Shake a leg!

555
00:47:18,379 --> 00:47:21,048
Well, well, well. What's that?

556
00:47:21,090 --> 00:47:24,677
Just a little hot supper
I fixed for you and the children.

557
00:47:24,635 --> 00:47:27,346
It seemed the least we could do.

558
00:47:28,681 --> 00:47:31,559
I won't have you worryin'
poor Mr. Powell another minute.

559
00:47:31,517 --> 00:47:34,729
Just look at you.
Dust and filth from top to toe.

560
00:47:34,729 --> 00:47:37,440
Want me to take 'em up
and wash 'em good?

561
00:47:37,440 --> 00:47:41,903
No, thank you, dear Icey.
Thank you. I'll tend to them.

562
00:47:41,819 --> 00:47:46,491
Don't be too hard on them, preacher.
Poor, motherless children.

563
00:47:46,449 --> 00:47:50,703
Remember now, Mr. Powell,
don't be afraid to call on us.

564
00:47:57,126 --> 00:48:00,129
Good-bye, Mrs. Spoon,
and thanks again.

565
00:48:08,012 --> 00:48:11,974
Now, weren't you afraid, little lambs,
down there in all that dark?

566
00:48:28,533 --> 00:48:31,035
They'll think it was me.

567
00:48:31,035 --> 00:48:34,372
They'll think it was
poor old Uncle Birdie.

568
00:48:37,083 --> 00:48:40,044
Oh, if you could've seen her, Bess.

569
00:48:41,128 --> 00:48:43,422
Down there in the deep place...

570
00:48:44,257 --> 00:48:47,009
with her hair wavin' soft and lazy...

571
00:48:47,051 --> 00:48:50,638
like meadow grass under floodwater.

572
00:48:51,806 --> 00:48:54,308
And that slit in her throat...

573
00:48:54,267 --> 00:48:57,019
like she had an extra mouth.

574
00:49:00,857 --> 00:49:04,777
You're the only human mortal
I can go to, Bess.

575
00:49:05,820 --> 00:49:10,324
If I go to the law,
they'll hang it on me.

576
00:49:16,414 --> 00:49:19,750
Sweet heaven,
save poor old Uncle Birdie.

577
00:49:25,798 --> 00:49:28,593
- I'm hungry.
- Sure.

578
00:49:28,593 --> 00:49:33,890
And there's fried chicken, sweet
potatoes, corn bread and apple cobbler.

579
00:49:34,891 --> 00:49:37,810
- Can I have my supper, please?
- Naturally.

580
00:49:37,810 --> 00:49:40,354
- Can I have milk too?
- Mm-hmm.

581
00:49:40,313 --> 00:49:43,858
But first we'll have a little talk
about our secrets.

582
00:49:43,816 --> 00:49:46,277
- No.
- And why not, pray tell?

583
00:49:46,277 --> 00:49:50,615
- 'Cause John said I mustn't.
- Never mind what John said!

584
00:49:50,573 --> 00:49:52,783
John's a meddler.

585
00:49:52,783 --> 00:49:55,203
Now, stop that snivelin'.

586
00:49:55,203 --> 00:49:58,331
Here. Do you know what that is?

587
00:49:58,331 --> 00:50:01,709
Want to see something cute?
Now look.

588
00:50:02,710 --> 00:50:05,505
How about that?

589
00:50:05,505 --> 00:50:08,341
This is what I use on meddlers.

590
00:50:08,341 --> 00:50:10,635
John might be a meddler.

591
00:50:10,676 --> 00:50:14,013
No! No, little lamb,
don't touch it.

592
00:50:13,971 --> 00:50:16,349
Don't touch my knif e.
That makes me mad.

593
00:50:16,307 --> 00:50:19,227
It makes me very, very mad.

594
00:50:19,227 --> 00:50:22,355
Now just tell me,
where's the money hid?

595
00:50:22,355 --> 00:50:24,899
But I swore, I promised John
I wouldn't tell.

596
00:50:24,899 --> 00:50:27,860
John doesn't matter!

597
00:50:27,819 --> 00:50:33,074
Can't I get that through your head,
you poor, silly disgusting wretch?

598
00:50:38,412 --> 00:50:41,123
There, now, you made me
lose my temper.

599
00:50:42,667 --> 00:50:45,336
I'm sorry. I'm real sorry.

600
00:50:46,546 --> 00:50:49,757
Just tell me, where's it hid, honey?

601
00:50:49,757 --> 00:50:52,343
- I'll tell.
- I told you to keep your mouth shut.

602
00:50:52,301 --> 00:50:55,096
It ain't fair to make Pearl tell
when she swore she wouldn't.

603
00:50:55,137 --> 00:50:58,391
- I'll tell.
- Well, I declare.

604
00:50:58,349 --> 00:51:02,395
Sometimes I think poor old John
might make it to heaven yet.

605
00:51:02,353 --> 00:51:03,938
All right, boy,
where's the money?

606
00:51:03,980 --> 00:51:08,192
In the cellar, buried
under a stone in the floor.

607
00:51:08,151 --> 00:51:10,319
It'll go hard if I find
you're lying, boy.

608
00:51:10,319 --> 00:51:12,864
I'm not lying.
Go look for yourself.

609
00:51:15,158 --> 00:51:16,617
All right.

610
00:51:27,003 --> 00:51:30,464
- Come along.
- What?

611
00:51:32,425 --> 00:51:35,761
Go ahead of me, the both of you.

612
00:51:35,761 --> 00:51:38,514
Down those stairs.

613
00:51:41,767 --> 00:51:44,353
You don't reckon I'd leave here,
do you, boy?

614
00:51:44,353 --> 00:51:48,649
- Don't you believe me?
- Why, sure, boy. Sure.

615
00:51:51,694 --> 00:51:52,862
Where, now?

616
00:51:52,904 --> 00:51:57,158
Mind, no tricks, now.
I can't abide a liar.

617
00:51:57,116 --> 00:51:58,659
Yonder.

618
00:52:01,996 --> 00:52:03,539
Oh, no, you don't.

619
00:52:08,836 --> 00:52:10,463
Now, where, boy? Where?

620
00:52:10,463 --> 00:52:13,257
Under the stone on the floor.

621
00:52:22,308 --> 00:52:25,645
- This is concrete!
- John made a sin.

622
00:52:25,603 --> 00:52:27,605
John told a lie.

623
00:52:30,316 --> 00:52:32,902
The Lord's a-talkin' to me now.

624
00:52:32,902 --> 00:52:34,612
He's a-sayin'...

625
00:52:34,695 --> 00:52:38,282
"A liar is an abomination
before Mine eyes."

626
00:52:39,951 --> 00:52:41,494
Speak, boy.
Where's it hid?

627
00:52:42,662 --> 00:52:44,622
Speak!

628
00:52:44,664 --> 00:52:46,749
Speak, or I'll cut your throat
and leave you to drip...

629
00:52:46,749 --> 00:52:48,793
like a hog hung up
in butcherin' time.

630
00:52:49,085 --> 00:52:52,547
Pearl, Shut up!
Pearl, You swore!

631
00:52:53,756 --> 00:52:55,591
You could save him, little bird.

632
00:52:55,633 --> 00:52:58,719
It's on my doll!

633
00:53:01,597 --> 00:53:03,558
The doll!

634
00:53:06,602 --> 00:53:08,896
Why, sure.

635
00:53:08,896 --> 00:53:11,274
Last place anybody'd think to look.

636
00:53:38,885 --> 00:53:40,386
Uncle Birdie Steptoe.

637
00:53:41,554 --> 00:53:45,766
Open that door, you spawn
of the devil's own strumpet!

638
00:54:13,127 --> 00:54:15,129
Uncle Birdie!

639
00:54:20,009 --> 00:54:22,929
Hide us, Uncle Birdie!
He's a-comin' with his knif e!

640
00:54:25,890 --> 00:54:30,228
It's me. John Harper and Pearl.
You told me to come.

641
00:54:30,186 --> 00:54:31,854
Oh, please!

642
00:54:31,854 --> 00:54:33,856
Please wake up!

643
00:54:33,856 --> 00:54:37,193
I swear on the Book,
I never done it.

644
00:54:37,193 --> 00:54:39,153
I never--

645
00:54:52,792 --> 00:54:55,002
There's still the river.

646
00:55:02,802 --> 00:55:04,011
The skiff is under the willows.

647
00:55:23,906 --> 00:55:25,074
Children!

648
00:57:07,176 --> 00:57:09,678
Once upon a time

649
00:57:09,720 --> 00:57:13,140
There was a pretty fly

650
00:57:13,098 --> 00:57:15,935
He had a pretty wife

651
00:57:15,935 --> 00:57:18,437
This pretty fly

652
00:57:19,271 --> 00:57:24,860
But one day she flew away

653
00:57:24,735 --> 00:57:28,906
Flew away

654
00:57:28,822 --> 00:57:31,951
She had two pretty

655
00:57:31,951 --> 00:57:34,787
Children

656
00:57:34,787 --> 00:57:36,997
But one night

657
00:57:37,039 --> 00:57:42,169
These two pretty children

658
00:57:42,086 --> 00:57:45,130
Flew away

659
00:57:48,592 --> 00:57:52,513
Into the sky

660
00:57:52,429 --> 00:57:58,519
Into the moon

661
00:58:13,701 --> 00:58:16,871
"Dear Walt and Icey,
I bet you've been worried...

662
00:58:16,871 --> 00:58:19,164
and gave us up for lost.

663
00:58:19,123 --> 00:58:21,333
Took the kids down here with me
for a visit...

664
00:58:21,375 --> 00:58:24,712
to my sister Elsie's farm.

665
00:58:24,670 --> 00:58:27,840
Thought a little change of scenery
would do us all a world of good...

666
00:58:27,798 --> 00:58:31,010
after so much trouble and heartache.

667
00:58:30,968 --> 00:58:34,972
At least the kids will get
a-plenty of good home cookin'.

668
00:58:34,889 --> 00:58:37,057
Your devoted Harry Powell."

669
00:58:37,099 --> 00:58:39,310
Now, ain't you relieved, Walt?

670
00:58:39,310 --> 00:58:41,645
Sure. But you was worried too, Mother.

671
00:58:41,645 --> 00:58:44,481
Takin' off with never a word
of good-bye.

672
00:58:44,481 --> 00:58:47,985
I got to figurin' maybe them gypsies
busted in and done off with all of them.

673
00:58:47,985 --> 00:58:50,613
You and your gypsies.
They've been gone a week.

674
00:58:50,571 --> 00:58:54,742
Sure. But not before one of them knif ed
a farmer and stole his horse.

675
00:58:54,700 --> 00:58:57,286
Never caught the gypsy,
nor the horse.

676
00:59:13,677 --> 00:59:16,931
Such times
when young 'uns run the roads.

677
00:59:16,889 --> 00:59:18,933
Go away, children.

678
00:59:25,814 --> 00:59:30,444
Hungry, I suppose. Well, I can't
spare you more than one potato apiece.

679
00:59:31,487 --> 00:59:34,198
- Where are your folks?
- I ain't got none.

680
00:59:34,156 --> 00:59:36,784
Oh, go away. Go away.

681
00:59:45,626 --> 00:59:49,129
An ungrateful child is an abomination
before the eyes of God.

682
00:59:49,046 --> 00:59:51,048
The world is fast
going to damnation...

683
00:59:51,048 --> 00:59:53,717
because of impudent young 'uns
flyin' in the face of age.

684
01:00:08,107 --> 01:00:10,401
I make soup out of them...

685
01:00:10,401 --> 01:00:13,112
but I wouldn't know how
to go about getting him open.

686
01:01:10,544 --> 01:01:12,963
We're gonna spend the night on land.

687
01:01:39,823 --> 01:01:44,036
Hush, little one

688
01:01:43,994 --> 01:01:46,539
Hush

689
01:01:47,998 --> 01:01:52,336
Hush, my little one

690
01:01:52,253 --> 01:01:55,214
Hush

691
01:01:56,382 --> 01:01:59,176
Morning soon

692
01:01:59,176 --> 01:02:03,973
Shall light your pillow

693
01:02:03,931 --> 01:02:07,059
Birds will sing

694
01:02:07,017 --> 01:02:09,436
In yonder

695
01:02:09,478 --> 01:02:12,022
Willow

696
01:02:12,022 --> 01:02:16,068
Hush, my little one

697
01:02:16,026 --> 01:02:18,737
Hush

698
01:02:19,905 --> 01:02:22,741
Are we going home now, John?

699
01:02:32,918 --> 01:02:37,006
Rest, dearest one

700
01:02:36,964 --> 01:02:39,925
Rest

701
01:02:41,302 --> 01:02:43,846
Rest here

702
01:02:43,888 --> 01:02:48,267
On my breast

703
01:02:49,727 --> 01:02:52,396
Little child

704
01:02:52,396 --> 01:02:57,401
With heart so brave

705
01:02:57,318 --> 01:02:59,904
Angel hosts

706
01:02:59,904 --> 01:03:05,075
Will keep you saf e

707
01:03:04,992 --> 01:03:09,330
Rest, my little one

708
01:03:09,246 --> 01:03:11,874
Rest

709
01:03:13,167 --> 01:03:17,838
Rest, little one

710
01:03:17,755 --> 01:03:20,966
Rest

711
01:03:59,338 --> 01:04:02,299
Leaning

712
01:04:05,553 --> 01:04:07,680
Saf e and secure

713
01:04:07,680 --> 01:04:11,976
From all alarm

714
01:04:11,934 --> 01:04:15,312
Leaning

715
01:04:18,357 --> 01:04:20,943
Leaning on

716
01:04:20,985 --> 01:04:23,571
The Everlasting

717
01:04:23,529 --> 01:04:25,739
Arm

718
01:04:25,781 --> 01:04:28,450
What a f ellowship

