Bring your baskets.

734
01:08:06,293 --> 01:08:08,295
Nicely picked, Clary.

735
01:08:08,337 --> 01:08:11,090
Mary, put the big ones on top.

736
01:08:11,090 --> 01:08:13,384
Ruby, most of them ain't fit
to go to market.

737
01:08:13,384 --> 01:08:16,720
Well, put your baskets down.
Ruby, run to the house...

738
01:08:16,720 --> 01:08:19,265
and f etch the tub
and put it by the pump.

739
01:08:19,223 --> 01:08:22,518
Clary, Mary, run up and f etch
a bar of laundry soap.

740
01:08:22,518 --> 01:08:25,187
- Yes, Miss Cooper.
- And a scrub brush.

741
01:08:25,187 --> 01:08:27,398
Come on up to the house, children.

742
01:08:29,441 --> 01:08:32,486
Gracious, if you ain't
a sight to beat all.

743
01:08:32,444 --> 01:08:34,446
Where are you from?

744
01:08:35,531 --> 01:08:37,074
Where are your folks?

745
01:08:37,157 --> 01:08:39,410
Come on. Speak up, now.

746
01:08:41,829 --> 01:08:44,748
Gracious, so I've got
two more mouths to f eed.

747
01:09:12,109 --> 01:09:14,445
Howdy, Miss Cooper.
What happened to our milk supply?

748
01:09:14,403 --> 01:09:16,280
Price of milk what it is,
not on your lif e.

749
01:09:16,322 --> 01:09:18,908
Do better makin' butter with the cream.
Sell it retail.

750
01:09:18,949 --> 01:09:21,368
Make smearcase for the children.
Feed what's left to my hogs.

751
01:09:22,494 --> 01:09:24,997
- She talks to herself.
- All the time.

752
01:09:25,039 --> 01:09:27,333
- Your ma's funny.
- She ain't our ma.

753
01:09:27,333 --> 01:09:30,294
- We just live at her house.
- Where are your folks?

754
01:09:30,252 --> 01:09:33,422
- Someplace.
- My daddy's in Detroit.

755
01:09:39,261 --> 01:09:42,973
Good morning, Miss Cooper. Guess what?
I'm savin' to buy you a charm bracelet.

756
01:09:42,932 --> 01:09:47,061
Never mind the talk. Don't forget your
visit Sunday. Come to church with us.

757
01:09:49,063 --> 01:09:51,649
See you Sunday, love.

758
01:09:51,649 --> 01:09:54,318
Take your baskets in, children.

759
01:09:54,318 --> 01:09:56,654
Reminiscent fools.

760
01:09:56,695 --> 01:09:58,113
All of 'em.

761
01:09:59,490 --> 01:10:00,866
Look there.

762
01:10:02,034 --> 01:10:05,079
She'll be losing her mind
to a tricky mouth and a full moon...

763
01:10:05,037 --> 01:10:08,791
and like as not,
I'll be saddled with the consequences.

764
01:10:09,542 --> 01:10:11,210
Here's what you owe me.

765
01:10:12,836 --> 01:10:15,089
One, two, three, four, five.

766
01:10:15,130 --> 01:10:17,383
Where's the other basket?
Where's Ruby?

767
01:10:17,383 --> 01:10:21,053
- She went.
- John, you go find Ruby.

768
01:10:21,011 --> 01:10:23,097
Big Ruby's my bothersome girl.

769
01:10:23,138 --> 01:10:25,099
She can't gather eggs
without bustin' 'em...

770
01:10:25,140 --> 01:10:28,060
but she's got mother hands with
a young 'un, so what are you to say?

771
01:10:30,062 --> 01:10:31,981
How about tonight, Ruby?

772
01:10:32,022 --> 01:10:35,442
- What gives?
- The old lady's around.

773
01:10:35,401 --> 01:10:36,819
How about Thursday?

774
01:10:38,529 --> 01:10:42,241
The old gal thinks she comes in
for sewing lessons on Thursday.

775
01:10:42,157 --> 01:10:44,285
Miss Cooper wants you.

776
01:10:47,997 --> 01:10:50,374
And will you show me
your dolly, little lady?

777
01:10:52,001 --> 01:10:54,670
- I see you got two more to your brood.
- Yeah...

778
01:10:54,670 --> 01:10:57,882
- and ornerier than the rest.
- How's your own boy, Miss Cooper?

779
01:10:57,840 --> 01:11:00,676
Haven't heard from Ralph
since Christmas. Don't matter, though.

780
01:11:00,634 --> 01:11:03,429
I've got a new crop.

781
01:11:03,429 --> 01:11:06,932
I'm a strong tree
with branches for many birds.

782
01:11:06,932 --> 01:11:10,436
I'm good for something in this world,
and I know it too.

783
01:11:33,584 --> 01:11:35,377
Now, old Pharaoh...

784
