he was king of Egypt-land.

785
01:11:38,297 --> 01:11:40,299
And he had a daughter.

786
01:11:40,299 --> 01:11:44,762
And once upon a time...

787
01:11:44,637 --> 01:11:47,848
she was walkin' along by the riverbank,
and she seen somethin'...

788
01:11:47,848 --> 01:11:50,809
bumpin' and scrapin' along
on a sandbar...

789
01:11:50,809 --> 01:11:52,520
down under the willows.

790
01:11:52,561 --> 01:11:55,523
- And you know what it was, children?
- No.

791
01:11:55,523 --> 01:11:58,734
Now, it was a skiff
washed up on the bar.

792
01:11:59,735 --> 01:12:03,280
- And who do you reckon was in it?
- Pearl and John.

793
01:12:04,198 --> 01:12:07,159
Not this time.
There was only one young 'un--

794
01:12:07,159 --> 01:12:09,662
a little boy babe.

795
01:12:09,620 --> 01:12:12,748
- And you know who he was, children?
- No.

796
01:12:14,458 --> 01:12:17,670
It was Moses, a king of men.

797
01:12:17,628 --> 01:12:20,464
Moses, children.

798
01:12:20,422 --> 01:12:22,883
Now, off to bed with you.

799
01:12:22,883 --> 01:12:25,052
John, get me an apple.

800
01:12:42,152 --> 01:12:44,572
And get one for yourself too.

801
01:12:57,543 --> 01:12:59,753
John, where are your folks?

802
01:12:59,795 --> 01:13:02,381
- Dead.
- Dead.

803
01:13:03,924 --> 01:13:06,010
Where you from?

804
01:13:06,051 --> 01:13:07,720
Upriver.

805
01:13:09,388 --> 01:13:13,684
Didn't figure you'd rode that skiff
all the way up from Parkersburg.

806
01:13:27,489 --> 01:13:30,075
Tell me that story again.

807
01:13:30,075 --> 01:13:33,287
Story? What story, honey?

808
01:13:33,287 --> 01:13:35,039
About them kings.

809
01:13:35,080 --> 01:13:38,959
And the queen found down on the sandbar
that time in the skiff.

810
01:13:38,918 --> 01:13:43,589
Kings? Why, there was only
one king, honey.

811
01:13:43,506 --> 01:13:46,509
I mind you said there was two.

812
01:13:46,509 --> 01:13:50,012
Well, shoot, now.
Maybe there was.

813
01:13:50,971 --> 01:13:53,724
Yes, come to think of it,
there was two.

814
01:14:19,959 --> 01:14:22,920
Must be Thursday.
Here comes Ruby.

815
01:14:29,885 --> 01:14:31,887
Here I go.

816
01:14:38,310 --> 01:14:40,688
Why, you're Ruby,
ain't you, my child?

817
01:14:40,688 --> 01:14:42,940
- Can I have this?
- Surely.

818
01:14:42,940 --> 01:14:45,985
- I'd like to talk to you, my dear.
- Will you buy me an ice cream?

819
01:14:45,985 --> 01:14:47,903
- Of course.
- Watch out, Preacher.

820
01:14:47,945 --> 01:14:51,115
- Why, Preacher!
- Shut your dirty mouths.

821
01:15:02,459 --> 01:15:05,504
-Ain't I pretty?
-You're the prettiest thing I've seen...

822
01:15:05,504 --> 01:15:08,007
in all my wanderin'.

823
01:15:07,965 --> 01:15:10,718
Ain't nobody ever told you that, Ruby?

824
01:15:10,718 --> 01:15:12,636
No one never did.

825
01:15:13,512 --> 01:15:16,390
There's two new ones
out at your place, ain't there?

826
01:15:16,348 --> 01:15:17,808
Uh-huh.

827
01:15:18,684 --> 01:15:21,145
- What's their names?
- Pearl and John.

828
01:15:22,938 --> 01:15:26,942
- Is there a doll?
- Only they never let me play with it.

829
01:15:34,617 --> 01:15:37,870
Did you ever see such pretty eyes
in all your born days?

830
01:15:37,828 --> 01:15:41,165
- Don't let him get away, sugar.
- He ain't like you all.

831
01:15:41,123 --> 01:15:44,251
Next time I won't even ask him
to buy me an ice cream.

832
01:15:52,927 --> 01:15:54,887
I's been bad.

833
01:15:58,766 --> 01:16:00,935
Ruby, you didn't have money
to buy this.

834
01:16:00,976 --> 01:16:03,687
- You'll whip me.
- When did I ever?

835
01:16:03,687 --> 01:16:06,899
- This man at the drugstore, he gave--
- The drugstore?

836
01:16:08,442 --> 01:16:12,112
Miss Cooper, I never been
to sewing lessons all them times.

837
01:16:12,071 --> 01:16:14,657
What you been up to, Ruby?

838
01:16:14,698 --> 01:16:16,742
I've been out with men.

839
01:16:18,577 --> 01:16:20,037
Child.

840
01:16:24,625 --> 01:16:28,838
You were looking for love, Ruby,
in the only foolish way you knew how.

841
01:16:33,133 --> 01:16:35,678
We all need love, Ruby.

842
01:16:35,636 --> 01:16:38,264
I lost the love of my son.

843
01:16:38,305 --> 01:16:40,474
I found it with you all.

844
01:16:42,309 --> 01:16:45,646
You're gonna grow up to be
a strong, fine woman...

845
01:16:45,646 --> 01:16:47,982
and I'm gonna see that you do.

846
01:16:48,023 --> 01:16:52,653
The gentleman weren't like them. He just
give me a book and buy me ice cream.

847
01:16:52,570 --> 01:16:55,781
- Now, who was this?
- He didn't ask me for nothin'.

848
01:16:55,781 --> 01:16:59,660
- What did you talk about?
- Pearl and John.

849
01:16:59,618 --> 01:17:02,955
John and Pearl?
Is he their pap?

850
01:17:02,913 --> 01:17:05,791
I don't know.

851
01:17:05,791 --> 01:17:08,210
Wonder why he hasn't been
to the house.

852
01:17:26,312 --> 01:17:29,648
- Miss Cooper! Miss Cooper!
- What?

853
01:17:29,648 --> 01:17:32,109
The man! The man!

854
01:17:36,197 --> 01:17:38,032
Good mornin', ladies.

855
01:17:38,032 --> 01:17:41,952
- How do?
- Why, you're Miss Cooper, I take it.

856
01:17:41,911 --> 01:17:44,330
It's about that John
and that Pearl?

857
01:17:44,371 --> 01:17:46,582
Oh, them poor little lambs.

858
01:17:46,582 --> 01:17:49,084
To think I never hoped to see them
again in this world.

859
01:17:49,126 --> 01:17:51,921
Oh, dear madam,
if you was to know...

860
01:17:51,879 --> 01:17:56,800
what a crown of thorns I've borne
in my search for them strayed chicks.

861
01:17:56,717 --> 01:17:58,928
Ruby, go f etch them kids.

862
01:18:02,139 --> 01:18:05,351
Oh, madam, I see
you're looking at my hands.

863
01:18:05,309 --> 01:18:07,353
Would you like me
to tell you a story...

864
01:18:07,353 --> 01:18:09,855
of left hand and right hand,
the tale of good and evil?

865
01:18:09,855 --> 01:18:12,858
It was with this left hand that
old brother Cain struck the blow...

866
01:18:12,858 --> 01:18:15,569
- that laid his brother low.
- Them kids is yours?

867
01:18:15,611 --> 01:18:19,782
- My own flesh and blood.
- Where's your missus?

868
01:18:19,698 --> 01:18:24,495
She run off with a drummer
during prayer meeting.

869
01:18:24,411 --> 01:18:26,664
- Where's she at?
- Down the river somewheres.

870
01:18:26,664 --> 01:18:30,334
Parkersburg or Cincinnati--
one of them Sodoms of the Ohio River.

871
01:18:30,292 --> 01:18:32,461
She took them kids with her?

872
01:18:32,503 --> 01:18:35,089
Heaven only knows
what unholy sights and sounds...

873
01:18:35,130 --> 01:18:37,132
them innocent
little babes has heard...

874
01:18:37,091 --> 01:18:39,552
in the dens of perdition
where she dragged 'em.

875
01:18:39,593 --> 01:18:43,472
Right funny, ain't it, how they rode
all the way upriver in a ten-foot boat?

876
01:18:46,100 --> 01:18:49,812
- Are they well, Miss Cooper?
- A sight better than they was.

877
01:18:51,230 --> 01:18:55,192
Gracious, gracious, you are
a good woman, Miss Cooper.

878
01:18:55,150 --> 01:18:57,820
How you figurin' to raise
them two without a woman?

879
01:18:57,778 --> 01:19:00,155
The Lord will provide.

880
01:19:00,197 --> 01:19:01,866
The Lord is merciful.

881
01:19:01,907 --> 01:19:04,285
Oh, what a day this is.

882
01:19:04,326 --> 01:19:06,370
And there's little John.

883
01:19:06,370 --> 01:19:09,290
- What's wrong, John?
- Come to me, boy.

884
01:19:09,290 --> 01:19:12,126
- What's wrong, John?
- Didn't you hear me, boy?

885
01:19:12,126 --> 01:19:14,753
John, when your dad says come,
you should mind him.

886
01:19:14,753 --> 01:19:16,755
He ain't my dad.

887
01:19:20,009 --> 01:19:23,262
No, and he ain't
no preacher, neither.

888
01:19:30,686 --> 01:19:33,689
Just march yourself yonder
to your horse, mister!

889
01:19:36,901 --> 01:19:38,736
March, mister!
I'm not foolin'!

890
01:19:42,281 --> 01:19:47,453
All right, but you haven't heard
the last of Harry Powell yet.

891
01:19:47,286 --> 01:19:50,748
The Lord God Jehovah will guide
my hand in vengeance!

892
01:19:52,374 --> 01:19:54,376
You devils!

893
01:19:55,836 --> 01:19:57,838
You whores of Babylon!

894
01:20:03,928 --> 01:20:06,514
I'll be back when it's dark.

