913
01:21:40,733 --> 01:21:45,362
Shame on you, Ruby, mooning around
the house after that mad dog of a man.

914
01:21:46,822 --> 01:21:49,116
Merciful heavens!

915
01:21:49,909 --> 01:21:53,078
Ruby, go get the children out of bed
and bring them down here.

916
01:21:55,789 --> 01:21:58,209
Women is such durn fools.

917
01:22:17,019 --> 01:22:20,022
It's a hard world for little things.

918
01:22:41,126 --> 01:22:45,381
Now, there was this sneaking
no-account, ornery King Herod.

919
01:22:45,339 --> 01:22:48,133
And when he heard tell of
little Jesus growin' up, he figured...

920
01:22:48,133 --> 01:22:51,470
"Well, shoot. There won't be
no room for the both of us.

921
01:22:51,428 --> 01:22:53,389
I'll just nip this in the bud."

922
01:22:53,430 --> 01:22:56,934
But he wasn't sure which of all those
babies in the land was King Jesus.

923
01:22:56,892 --> 01:22:59,478
So that cruel old
King Herod figured...

924
01:22:59,478 --> 01:23:03,315
if he killed all the babies in the land,
he'd be sure and get little Jesus.

925
01:23:03,274 --> 01:23:06,485
And when little King Jesus' ma and pa
heard about this plan...

926
01:23:06,485 --> 01:23:09,280
- what do you reckon they went and done?
- They hid in a broom closet.

927
01:23:09,280 --> 01:23:13,450
- They hid under the porch.
- No. They went a-runnin'.

928
01:23:13,367 --> 01:23:17,329
Well, now, John, you're right.
That's just what they done.

929
01:23:17,288 --> 01:23:19,874
Little King Jesus' ma and pa
saddled a mule...

930
01:23:19,832 --> 01:23:22,418
and they rode all the way down
into Egypt-land.

931
01:23:22,376 --> 01:23:25,880
Yeah. And that's where the queen
found them in the billy rushes.

932
01:23:25,838 --> 01:23:29,133
Oh, no. That wasn't the same story
at all. That was little King Moses.

933
01:23:29,133 --> 01:23:33,137
But just the same, it did seem like
it was plague time for little ones.

934
01:23:33,053 --> 01:23:36,182
Them olden days.
Them hard, hard times.

935
01:23:42,938 --> 01:23:44,940
Figured I was gone, huh?

936
01:23:44,982 --> 01:23:48,027
Run! Hide in the staircase!
Run quick!

937
01:23:47,985 --> 01:23:50,404
Ruby, get!

938
01:23:50,446 --> 01:23:53,616
- What do you want?
- I want them kids.

939
01:23:53,574 --> 01:23:56,785
- What do you want them for?
- That's none of your business, madam.

940
01:23:56,785 --> 01:24:00,039
I'm givin' you till the count of three
to get out of here, then I'm shootin'!

941
01:24:15,846 --> 01:24:18,140
Miss Booher? Rachel Cooper.

942
01:24:18,140 --> 01:24:20,309
Get your state troopers
out to my place.

943
01:24:20,309 --> 01:24:22,937
I got something trapped
in my barn.

944
01:24:33,364 --> 01:24:36,534
- I'll go see to Pearl.
- I'll make coff ee.

945
01:24:46,168 --> 01:24:48,128
She's all right.

946
01:24:50,256 --> 01:24:52,591
John, you know, when you're little,
you have more endurance...

947
01:24:52,633 --> 01:24:55,344
than God is ever
to grant you again?

948
01:24:55,344 --> 01:24:58,472
Children are man at his strongest.
They abide.

949
01:25:12,987 --> 01:25:15,823
- Why didn't you call us before now?
- Didn't want your dirty shoes...

950
01:25:15,823 --> 01:25:18,158
- trackin' up my clean floors.
- Is that him, ma'am?

951
01:25:18,200 --> 01:25:21,161
Yes. Mind where you shoot, boys.
There are children here.

952
01:25:21,120 --> 01:25:24,999
Harry Powell, you're under arrest
for the murder of Willa Harper.

953
01:25:26,959 --> 01:25:28,335
Drop that knif e.

954
01:25:30,838 --> 01:25:31,797
Don't!

955
01:25:37,928 --> 01:25:40,514
Here, here, take it back!

956
01:25:40,556 --> 01:25:44,476
Take it back! I don't want it, Dad!
It's too much!

957
01:25:44,393 --> 01:25:45,769
Here!

958
01:25:56,447 --> 01:25:59,325
Lynch him!

959
01:25:59,325 --> 01:26:02,328
- Bluebeard!
- Twenty-five wives!

960
01:26:02,286 --> 01:26:04,121
And he killed them all!

961
01:26:04,163 --> 01:26:07,291
- If the people of Marshall County--
- Bluebeard!

962
01:26:13,797 --> 01:26:16,300
Will you identify the prisoner?

963
01:26:16,342 --> 01:26:20,554
Please, little lad, won't you look
yonder and tell the court...

964
01:26:20,471 --> 01:26:23,140
if that is the man
that killed your mother?

965
01:26:30,397 --> 01:26:34,318
It's all right, Mrs. Cooper.
You can take the little f ellow away.

966
01:26:34,276 --> 01:26:36,695
Merry Christmas to you and yours,
Mrs. Cooper.

967
01:26:36,695 --> 01:26:39,949
And what's Santa Claus going to bring
you for Christmas, little man?

968
01:26:40,950 --> 01:26:42,785
Bluebeard!

969
01:26:51,669 --> 01:26:54,630
- There's Pearl!
- Get your coats.

970
01:26:54,588 --> 01:26:56,757
Them's her orphans!

971
01:26:56,799 --> 01:26:58,467
- Where's Ruby?
- She went.

972
01:26:58,509 --> 01:27:01,470
Them poor little lambs!

973
01:27:01,428 --> 01:27:05,766
Them is the ones
he sinned against, my friends!

974
01:27:05,724 --> 01:27:07,685
Go out the back door!

975
01:27:11,647 --> 01:27:14,275
Ain't we goin' to the bus depot?

976
01:27:15,568 --> 01:27:19,196
Draggin' the name of the Lord
through the evil mud of his soul!

977
01:27:19,154 --> 01:27:23,492
- String that Bluebeard up to a post!
- He's Satan hiding behind the cross!

978
01:27:23,450 --> 01:27:25,286
Come on!

979
01:28:10,331 --> 01:28:13,959
I love him.
You think he's like them others.

980
01:28:19,840 --> 01:28:21,967
You were so mad, you shot him!

981
01:28:38,067 --> 01:28:39,652
- Hey, Bart.
- Yeah?

982
01:28:39,735 --> 01:28:43,697
- We're savin' this bird up for you.
- This time it'll be a privilege.

983
01:29:09,598 --> 01:29:12,268
I'm glad they didn't send me nothin'.
Whenever they do, it's nothin' I want...

984
01:29:12,268 --> 01:29:16,063
but just somethin' to show me how fancy
and smart they've come up in the world.

985
01:29:22,653 --> 01:29:25,573
- Can we give you your presents now?
- Shoot.

986
01:29:25,531 --> 01:29:28,242
You don't mean to say
you got me a present.

987
01:29:28,242 --> 01:29:29,910
Shoot, now.

988
01:29:38,127 --> 01:29:40,421
A potholder.

989
01:29:40,462 --> 01:29:43,465
And it's much neater
than last year, Ruby.

990
01:29:46,844 --> 01:29:48,929
Another potholder!

991
01:29:48,929 --> 01:29:52,474
Now, ain't that thoughtful.
I'm always burning my hands.

992
01:29:54,518 --> 01:29:57,563
This doesn't look basted.
This looks made!

993
01:29:58,522 --> 01:30:01,233
And you finished the edge
with a chain-stitch.

994
01:30:01,233 --> 01:30:03,402
Oh, that's just dandy, Clary.

995
01:30:06,113 --> 01:30:08,115
Another potholder?

996
01:30:13,329 --> 01:30:16,248
Oh, now, did you two
make this together?

997
01:30:16,248 --> 01:30:17,917
You helped us some.

998
01:30:27,051 --> 01:30:30,179
That's the richest gift
a body could have.

999
01:30:31,096 --> 01:30:35,059
And your presents are in the cupboard
under the china closet.

1000
01:30:40,105 --> 01:30:42,107
This is yours.

1001
01:30:57,915 --> 01:31:00,751
Lord, save little children.

1002
01:31:00,709 --> 01:31:03,963
You'd think the world would be ashamed
to name such a day as Christmas...

1003
01:31:03,921 --> 01:31:07,049
for one of them and then go on
in the same old way.

1004
01:31:08,300 --> 01:31:13,013
My soul is humbled when I see the way
little ones accept their lot.

1005
01:31:14,223 --> 01:31:16,517
Lord, save little children.

1006
01:31:16,517 --> 01:31:19,854
The wind blows,
and the rains are cold.

1007
01:31:19,812 --> 01:31:21,564
Yet they abide.

1008
01:31:50,217 --> 01:31:52,595
That watch is sure
a fine, loud ticker.

1009
01:31:54,430 --> 01:31:58,184
Be nice to have someone around the house
who can give me the right time of day.

1010
01:31:59,310 --> 01:32:02,646
This watch is the nicest watch
I ever had.

1011
01:32:02,605 --> 01:32:06,567
Well, a fellow can't just go around
with run-down, busted watches.

1012
01:32:13,490 --> 01:32:16,076
They abide and they endure.